                            <comment id="197374" author="adilger" created="Mon, 29 May 2017 03:53:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Close old ticket.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="46473" author="yong.fan" created="Fri, 12 Oct 2012 10:49:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Another similar failure instance:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/0d741d06-1413-11e2-b63d-52540035b04c&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/0d741d06-1413-11e2-b63d-52540035b04c&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;All the shown sub-tests are marked as &quot;PASS&quot;, but the whole test is marked as &quot;ABORT&quot;, without further logs, which is similar as &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-1401&quot; title=&quot;sanity test passed but it&amp;#39;s marked ABORT&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-1401&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-1401&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="39581" author="mdiep" created="Wed, 30 May 2012 11:58:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I believe it&apos;s correct to mark the entire testsuite to fail when there is a missing status in a subtest (test_iorfpp). &lt;br/&gt;
As to why test_iorfpp&apos;s log was not there, I don&apos;t know. But the testsuite output show test_iorfpp started.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It seems that the previous iorssf passed but hit some sort of issue because autotest dump stacktrace at the end&lt;br/&gt;
Unfortunately, there was nothing in the console and the conman hasn&apos;t recorded any console since 4/15&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
